56.4	Haussmann's_renovation_of_Paris	Haussmann's renovation of Paris	Haussmann's Renovation of Paris, or the Haussmann Plan, was a modernization program of Paris commissioned by Napoléon III and led by the Seine prefect, Baron Georges-Eugène Haussmann, between 1853 and 1870. Though work continued until the end of the 19th century, well after the Second Empire's demise in 1870, it is often referred to as the "Second Empire reforms".	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f8/Blv-haussmann-lafayette.jpg/250px-Blv-haussmann-lafayette.jpg
